# Plan Adherence

Before implementing any feature, creating any file, or adding any dependency, verify it
traces to the approved product plan.

## Feature Scope

All implementation work must map to an approved feature in `docs/feature-list.md`:

| Feature | Scope |
|---------|-------|
| F1 | RFdiffusion CDR backbone generation |
| F2 | ProteinMPNN sequence design |
| F3 | RF2 in-silico validation |
| F4 | TCR-MHC prediction mode |
| F5 | Full pipeline orchestration (F1→F2→F3) |
| F6 | Model weight management (internal) |
| F7 | Batch design generation |
| F8 | Fine-tuning (all 3 models) |
| F9 | Multi-GPU inference |

If work does not map to F1–F9, raise `[Scope Drift]` via AskQuestion:
- Cite the code or file being created
- Explain which feature it was intended for
- First option: "Map to feature FN — here's why..."
- Last option: "Let me explain / provide more context"

### Out of Scope (do not implement)

- Rosetta scoring / PyRosetta (ddG/SAP) — permanently excluded per R2 and ADR-006
- Training from scratch — fine-tuning only (F8)
- Web UI / dashboard — API-only via Modal
- Distributed multi-machine inference — single-container multi-GPU only (F9)

## Component Verification

New files must map to an approved component from `docs/spec.md` §Component Overview:

| Component | Expected Location |
|-----------|------------------|
| Modal App | `src/app.py` |
| RFdiffusion Stage | `src/rfdiffusion_stage.py` | <!-- ADR-002: flat modules -->
| ProteinMPNN Stage | `src/proteinmpnn_stage.py` | <!-- ADR-002: flat modules -->
| RF2 Stage | `src/rf2_stage.py` | <!-- ADR-002: flat modules -->
| Config Module | `src/config.py` |
| Pipeline Orchestrator | `src/pipeline.py` |
| Output Packaging | `src/output.py` |
| Weight Manager | `src/weights.py` |
| Fine-Tune Module | `src/finetune/` |
| Tests | `tests/` (mirroring `src/` structure) |

Files outside these locations require justification. Raise `[Scope Drift]` if a new
component is being introduced that isn't in the spec.

## Dependency Verification

Before adding any new dependency, check `docs/dependency-inventory.md`. If the dependency
is not listed:
1. Raise `[Decision]` with a recommendation
2. On approval, back-add to `docs/dependency-inventory.md`
3. Append to the Resolution Log in `docs/research-brief.md`
